  "body": "## Fixes #57184 \r\n\r\n## What this PR does\r\nImproves the summary display of `GenericMemoryRef` so that `BoundsError` messages show the effective accessible length from the current reference offset.\r\n\r\n## Why\r\nWhen a `MemoryRef` is created at a non-zero offset, the existing `BoundsError` message can be misleading because it only shows the type. Displaying the remaining accessible length makes the error more actionable and aligns the behavior with other types like `SubString`.\r\n\r\n## Implementation details\r\n- Adds a `Base.summary` method for `GenericMemoryRef` in `base/show.jl`\r\n- Computes remaining length using `parent(ref)` and `Core.memoryrefoffset(ref)`\r\n- Does not change bounds checking logic or error types\r\n- Adds focused tests in `test/errorshow.jl` to validate the improved error output",
